532
00:23:29.400 --> 00:23:31.880
from the entire committee to you.

533
00:23:31.880 --> 00:23:35.120
Are there any final remarks that you would like to make?

534
00:23:35.120 --> 00:23:37.160
No, it's been a pleasure, as always,

535
00:23:37.160 --> 00:23:39.280
to come and talk with you about our work.

536
00:23:39.280 --> 00:23:41.800
My whole team is very passionate about what we do,

537
00:23:41.800 --> 00:23:44.320
because we are working for the greater good of New Zealanders,

538
00:23:44.320 --> 00:23:46.040
which is always very satisfying,

539
00:23:46.040 --> 00:23:49.800
but I would end by reiterating my comments

540
00:23:49.800 --> 00:23:52.120
that you are a classic cross-party mechanism.

541
00:23:52.120 --> 00:23:55.040
There are ways, I think, that committees can help

542
00:23:55.040 --> 00:23:59.160
drive a conversation that gets out of the silos

543
00:23:59.160 --> 00:24:02.240
and into what's better for long-term thinking.

544
00:24:02.240 --> 00:24:04.000
Thank you so much. Thank you.

545
00:24:04.000 --> 00:24:05.840
I appreciate you, thank you.
